The paper deals with domain adaptation, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of "Learning" (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on heterogeneous domain adaptation, which involves different feature spaces, and thus, it is likely to fall under "Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition" (cs.CV) and "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) subcategories. The proposed method also involves preserving the structural information of the original data, which is related to "Natural Language Processing" (cs.CL) and "Multimedia" (cs.MM) subcategories.
